<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-05-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-05-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="1179" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1179">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.113/4130</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Governor of Arizona</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Executive Office</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Phoenix</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-05-03">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 3, 1916</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge receipt
                            of your letter of the 28th ult., requesting the cooperation of the
                            proper officials in preventing the smuggling of arms and ammunition from
                            Arizona into Mexico.</p>
                        <p>You may be assured that I will immediately communicate with the proper
                            officers of those Arizona counties contiguous to the international
                            boundary, urging them to adopt all measures necessary to prevent illicit
                            traffic in firearms and ammunition.</p>
                        <p>Very respectfully,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Geo. W. P. Hunt</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>